 Review comment:
   @wesm I can change this, but it's worth mentioning that what I've written is how Java (and incompletely: Go, JS) serialize metadata. Furthermore, key value entries are compared in key sorted order in C++ (so key value reordering does not matter). Is there a use case for duplicated metadata keys? It seems we might prefer to require that they be unique, since all reference implementations currently do. Either way, this probably warrants a mailing list discussion.

